name: NOMOSAPIENS
tagline: (n) people eating with awareness of food; see LCHF
body:
### Welcome

Write in GitHub Flavored Markdown, pick a template, and publish. You can check out the published branch with:

```
$ cd your_repo_root/repo_name
$ git fetch origin
$ git checkout gh-pages
```

If you're using the GitHub for Mac, simply sync your repository and you'll see the new branch.

### Details
The `gh-pages` branch in your repository is where you can post HTML content, with Jekyll supplements, for site-wide headers and footers without having to copy them across every page, intelligent blog support and other template features like @mention for links to profiles like @johan, the owner of this page. [Docs](https://help.github.com/pages)
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
